review_comments.body:
![critical](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/critical.svg)

The encoding for RIP-relative `mov` instructions (`mov reg, [rip+label]`) is incorrect.

1.  The instruction length is 7 bytes, but the relative offset calculation uses a length of 5 bytes (`curOff + pos + 5`). It should be `curOff + pos + 7`.
2.  The relocation offset passed to `addReloc` is `curOff + pos + 1`, which points to the opcode. It should be `curOff + pos + 3`, pointing to the start of the 32-bit displacement field.

These errors will result in incorrect relocations and broken executables.

```suggestion
              const rel32 = targetOff - (curOff + pos + 7);
              buf.push(rel32 & 0xFF, (rel32 >> 8) & 0xFF, (rel32 >> 16) & 0xFF, (rel32 >> 24) & 0xFF);
            } else {
              buf.push(0, 0, 0, 0);
              addReloc(curOff + pos + 3, labelName, 2, -4);
            }
```

