![high](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/high-priority.svg)

The `encLea` function only handles memory operands with 8-bit displacements (`mod === 1`). It's missing the case for 32-bit displacements (`mod === 2`), which will lead to incorrect encoding for memory operands with large offsets.

```typescript
function encLea(buf: number[], dst: string, mem: string): number {
  const dr = regIndex(dst);
  if (dr < 0) return 0;
  const m = parseMem(mem);
  if (!m) return 0;
  const pos = buf.length;
  buf.push(...emitRex(1, isExtReg(dst) ? 1 : 0, 0, m.rexB));
  buf.push(0x8D);
  buf.push(modrm(m.mod, dr, m.rm));
  if (m.mod === 1) {
    buf.push(m.disp & 0xFF);
  } else if (m.mod === 2) {
    buf.push(m.disp & 0xFF, (m.disp >> 8) & 0xFF, (m.disp >> 16) & 0xFF, (m.disp >> 24) & 0xFF);
  }
  return buf.length - pos;
}
```

